Class InlineAssociationDeserializer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonDeserializer<T>
      • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.StdDeserializer<T>
        • uk.co.blackpepper.bowman.InlineAssociationDeserializer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type or a supertype of the type that this deserializer is intended for - not needed by client code
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.ContextualDeserializer, com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.NullValueProvider, Serializable
    public class InlineAssociationDeserializer<T>
extends com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.std.StdDeserializer<T>
implements com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.deser.ContextualDeserializer
    A Jackson deserializer to properly handle inline associations in an annotated entity type. A proxy will be created for the annotated property, allowing the resolution of further linked associations.

    Assign this deserializer to a property with @JsonDeserialize(contentUsing = InlineAssociationDeserializer.class).

    Author:
    Ryan Pickett
